                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Aufidius Aprilis <lb n="2"/>c<supplied reason="lost">or</supplied>inthiarius <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">de thea</supplied>tro Balbi <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">sibi</supplied> et <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">Gargili</supplied>ae Secundae <lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">uxo</supplied>ri sanctissimae et <lb n="7"/><supplied reason="lost">Gar</supplied>giliae <expan><abbr>Sp</abbr><ex>uri</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan> Venustae <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> Antoni <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilii</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Pap</abbr><ex>iria</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/>Flacci liberti Felicis <lb n="10"/>uxori piissimae et <lb n="11"/><expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arco</ex></expan> Antonio Felici
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Erster inschriftlicher Beleg mit Nennung des Theatrum Balbi. Der Altar steht auf Sockel aus Travertin. (Weitere Inschrift des L. Aufidius Aprilis vgl. S. Panciera, NSA 1975, 222-224 = AE 1977, 24). Material: lunensischer Marmor.</p>
            </div>
